{
  "texts": [
    "The external tool can then process this request, generate a corresponding response, and send it back to LLM.",
    "The response from the external tool is considered an observation (O) of the LLM.",
    "Observations may be the correct information that the model needs or error logs generated during request processing.",
    "They are provided as history messages to the next round of the model.",
    "Such interactions can help the LLM expand its functionality and integrate external tools and services."
  ]
}